1 Introduction
**************

BashStyle-NG is a graphical utility and toolchain for changing the look,
feel, and behavior of ‘Bash’, ‘Readline’, ‘Vim’, ‘Nano’, and ‘Git’.  It
acts as a central hub to inject advanced features and visual
enhancements into standard command-line tools, making the terminal
environment more user-friendly and powerful.

   The following is summary of possibilities, see the documentation for
more.

Visual Prompt Customization
===========================

   • Prompt Styles: Includes 12 pre-defined prompt designs which can be
     randomized per session or customized.
   • Custom Prompt Builder: A modular builder inside the GUI allows
     users to create their own custom prompt layouts, or modify the
     predefined styles.
   • Color Schemes: Full control over text and prompt colors, with
     optional monochrome modes.

Utility Enhancements
====================

   • Colored Output: Forces colored rendering for traditional manpages,
     ‘ls’, ‘gcc’ error messages and ‘grep’ matches.
   • Directory Tracking: Features a custom ‘lscd’ command that remembers
     the last visited directories, auto-restores sessions, and prints
     directory contents immediately after navigating.
   • Git Status Integration: dynamically displays the current Git
     branch, revision, action, and more straight in the prompt.
   • History: customize how many commands the shell remembers, ignores
     duplicate entries, and controls how history is written to disk.
     This includes the options for ‘history isolation’ - meaning that
     terminal sessions have no outside visible history.  Or the opposite
     ‘history sync’, when active, reloading the prompt (pressing enter),
     will load any new history created from other sessions.

Git repository access
=====================

You can get the latest in-development version by running

   • git clone <git://gitlab.com/Nanolx/bashstyle-ng.git>

